@Node "Introduction"

                      @{fg fill}Introduction@{fg shadow}

 Orpsw is a security controller. It puts a password to hard
 disk to protect the Dos environment. If you want to access
 the hard disk using Dos, you have to enter the password.
 Orpsw is also a window activator.
@endnode

@Node "Requirements"

 @{fg fill}Requirements:@{fg shadow}
 A hard disk, Kickstart 3.0, M68020

 @{fg fill}Tested at these systems:@{fg shadow}
 A1200, 2.5" hard disk.
@endnode

@Node "Installation"

                        @{fg fill}Installation@{fg shadow}

 Execute HDToolBox. Dont forget to note the old partition
 info to not to have a risk of destroying data. Change
 the Dos types of all partitions to 0x444F5308. Then pass
 to 'Add new file systems' menu. Load the Orpsw file
 system. Change its file system like above. And something
 last. Save all the changes. To remove Orpsw, delete the
 file system that you have changed its Dos type like
 above and set Dos types of partitions to FastFileSystem.
@endnode

@Node "Other Features"

                     @{fg fill}Other Features@{fg shadow}

 - Prevents floppy drive clicks and sets retry count 1.

 - You can use '*' instead of AmigaDos wildcard chars '#?'.
   Important: If you use '*' alone it means the default
   window, so that things change a little. Because of that
   you are adviced to use double stars. For example use
   'LIST **' instead of 'LIST *'. 'Copy console: file'
   command writes the informatin taken from console to the
   specified file. For eof press ctrl-backslash.

 - Orpsw is also a window activator. Instead mouse pointer,
   front screen is used for activation. Now, you must
   remove other window activators like AutoPoint.
@endnode

@Node "Hints and tips"

                     @{fg fill}Hints And Tips@{fg shadow}

 - If your partition doesn't startup because of a reason
   or seems like it isn't mounted, load HDToolBox & change
   types to FFS. Be sure that nothing happens to your Dos
   informations so forget the format command.

 - If you have to format your drive, firstly change the
   partition Dos type to FFS. After format, change it
   to the one above.

 - If you see yellow & black lines at boot, remove Orpsw. 

 - Orpsw asks password once after power on reset.

 - If you enter 'RESET' as the password, reset & kill sys
   is done.

 - There are two passwords. The first is 'AAAAAAAA' and
   second is 'BBBBBBBB'. You can also check which password
   is entered from Startup-Sequence and control them.

 - You can change passwords with a hex editor. Password
   length is 8 chars including spaces, and must be left
   justified and padded with blanks. Case not important.

 - There are two versions for VGA and PAL monitors.
@endnode

